title: Natural gas consumption in the United States : 1995 to 2018
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Consumption in trillion cubic feet, containing a total of 16 data points.
In general Consumption in trillion cubic feet has rose over the Year.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2017 and 2018.
Maximum Consumption in trillion cubic feet, about 29.95 was reported at Year 2018
Minimum Consumption in trillion cubic feet about 21.7 was reached at Year 2006
